==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cassiterite
<hw>Cas*sit"er*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
tin.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>Native tin dioxide; tin stone; a
mineral occurring in tetragonal crystals of reddish brown color, and
brilliant adamantine luster; also massive, sometimes in compact forms
with concentric fibrous structure resembling wood (<stype>wood
tin</stype>), also in rolled fragments or pebbly (<stype>Stream
tin</stype>). It is the chief source of metallic tin. See <er>Black
tin</er>, under <er>Black</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cassius</ent>⟦br⟧
